f=Cybersecurity/veil/marketplace/data-classification/SKILL.md · in=Risk-based data asset classification framework defines information categorized, handled, protected based sensitivity criticality organization. classification system ensures appropriate security controls applied proportional value risk associated asset. · p=Without clear classification, data treated equally which means either sensitive data under-protected low-risk data over-protected (wasting resources). classification framework ensures data protection resources applied they matter most, everyone organization understands handle type information. · wu=Classifying new dataset, system, information asset., Determining what security controls apply specific data type., Onboarding new vendor partner what data they handle?, Training policy documentation helping teams understand classification., Auditing existing data storage handling practices. · h3:PUBLIC=**Definition:** Information explicitly approved public release. confidentiality requirement; integrity availability still relevant. **Examples:** · h3:PUBLIC=Published marketing materials, Public press releases, Public website content, Published research papers · h3:PUBLIC=**Security Controls:** · h3:PUBLIC=Integrity controls prevent unauthorized modification, Availability controls business need, No confidentiality restrictions · h3:INTERNAL=**Definition:** Information sensitive intended public distribution. Internal business operations data. **Examples:** · h3:INTERNAL=Internal policies and procedures, Organizational charts, Internal communications (non-sensitive), General operational data · h3:INTERNAL=**Security Controls:** · h3:INTERNAL=Access limited employees authorized contractors, Basic access controls (authentication required), No unauthorized external distribution · h3:CONFIDENTIAL=**Definition:** Sensitive business information whose unauthorized disclosure cause moderate harm organization, customers, partners. **Examples:** · h3:CONFIDENTIAL=Customer personally identifiable information (PII), Financial records and reports, Business plans and strategies, Intellectual property (not trade secret), Employee HR data · h3:CONFIDENTIAL=**Security Controls:** · h3:CONFIDENTIAL=Access strict need-to-know basis, Encryption rest transit, Data Loss Prevention (DLP) monitoring, Access logging and auditing, Minimum years retention audit/compliance data · h3:RESTRICTED=**Definition:** Highly sensitive information whose unauthorized disclosure cause severe harm, including legal liability, regulatory penalties, significant competitive disadvantage. **Examples:** · h3:RESTRICTED=Trade secrets core, Passwords, cryptographic keys, credentials, Board communications strategic M&A data, Health records special category data (GDPR Art., Payment card data (PCI DSS scope) · h3:RESTRICTED=**Security Controls:** · h3:RESTRICTED=Strict need-to-know formal access approval, Strong encryption (AES-256 equivalent) rest transit, Hardware Security Module (HSM) cryptographic material applicable, Continuous monitoring and alerting, Mandatory access logging alerting unauthorized access attempts, Data retention: minimum years regulatory requirement · h2:Classification Decision Tree=information explicitly approved public release? **PUBLIC** information intended internal use? **INTERNAL** unauthorized disclosure cause harm? Yes **CONFIDENTIAL** unauthorized disclosure cause severe harm (legal, financial, reputational)? Yes **RESTRICTED** special category data (health, biometric, political, religious)? **RESTRICTED** (or required regulation) · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\| Action \| PUBLIC \| INTERNAL \| CONFIDENTIAL \| RESTRICTED \| · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\| **Storage** \| No restriction \| Standard storage \| Encrypted storage \| Encrypted + access controlled \| · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\| **Transmission** \| No restriction \| TLS recommended \| TLS required \| TLS + additional controls \| · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\| **Retention** \| As needed \| As needed \| Min 5 years \| Min 7 years or regulatory \| · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\| **Disposal** \| No restriction \| Standard secure deletion \| Secure deletion (overwrite) \| Physical destruction or certified wipe \| · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\| **Access logging** \| Not required \| Recommended \| Required \| Required + alerting \| · h2:Data Handling Requirements=\| **Third-party sharing** \| No restriction \| NDA required \| NDA + security assessment \| NDA + assessment + contractual controls \| · of=`## Data Classification: [asset/data set name] \· Classification: [PUBLIC / INTERNAL / CONFIDENTIAL / RESTRICTED] \· Rationale: [decision tree path used] \· Handling: [storage \· transmission \· retention \· disposal] \· Access: [who can access \· how access is granted \· review cadence]` · pr=**Classify creation.** piece data classified it's created, retroactively. **When doubt, default higher.** classification isn't clear, mark CONFIDENTIAL until reviewed. **Protection follows classification.** Security controls tied classification tiers automate enforcement possible. **Review reclassify.** Data sensitivity changes over time; periodic reviews ensure classification remains accurate. **Classification without handling theatre.** label without enforcement meaningless. · f=**Unclassified data** treat INTERNAL default; flag classification review., **Mixed classification dataset** treat highest applicable tier., **Regulatory override** regulation requires stricter handling classification suggests, regulation wins (e.g., GDPR personal data even classified INTERNAL). · b:with Other Skills=**veil's privacy-by-design** (sibling): uses classification tiers input DPIA privacy controls., **veil's DLP** (sibling): DLP policies enforce egress controls classification tier., **veil's breach-notification** (sibling): classification determines severity breach notification obligations., **dana (Engineering)**: data store designs implement encryption access controls tier., **warden**: classification gaps (unclassified data, incorrect tiers) register risks., **Hack23/cia companion skills**: `data-protection`, `data-classification`, `gdpr`, `privacy-policy` reference tiers.